name: ABC
text: NEW: Federal appeals court upholds a six-day extension for counting absentee ballots in Wisconsin’s presidential election. The Republican National Committee, state GOP and Wisconsin Republican legislators had argued against the deadline extension. https://t.co/LW0HMTZwMh

name: ABC
text: WATCH LIVE: Pres. Trump and Joe Biden are set to take the stage for the first presidential debate in Cleveland. Follow along for continuing, live coverage on @ABCNewsLive. https://t.co/wW9UIusz63

name: ABC
text: New data shows American adults have sharply increased their alcohol consumption during the COVID-19 crisis, drinking on more days per month, and to greater excess. Heavy drinking among women especially has soared. https://t.co/mruETfAvJE

name: ABC
text: .@GStephanopoulos: Despite a tumultuous year that has seen an impeachment, a global pandemic, social unrest and more, "this presidential race has been remarkably stable." https://t.co/5Bl4Ob3O2t #Debates2020 https://t.co/8R8JyuiIHA

name: ABC
text:
Trump vs. Biden on the issues:

ECONOMY: https://t.co/QQ8wTRimP9

HEALTH CARE: https://t.co/A5MxAX5T0g

name: ABC
text: Joe Biden leads Pres. Trump 54-45% among likely voters in Pennsylvania, new @ABC News/WaPo poll finds, thanks in large part to a 2-1 lead in the Philadelphia suburbs. https://t.co/H2KWY45C2A

name: ABC
text:
Debate moderator Chris Wallace selected the topics, with each segment getting about 15 minutes:

• The candidates' records
• The Supreme Court
• COVID-19
• The economy
• Race and violence in U.S. cities
• Integrity of the election

https://t.co/wEmaghEXNG #Debates2020

name: ABC
text: Asked by @GStephanopoulos "How much will this debate matter?" @matthewjdowd says: "Joe Biden would like this debate not to matter. Donald Trump needs this debate to matter." https://t.co/5Bl4Ob3O2t #Debates2020 https://t.co/Ek7r2UsVzr

name: ABC
text: "Her death was preventable, if only we knew the danger that lurked in her room." https://t.co/BnHnLCPqhB

name: ABC
text: RT @ABCPolitics: .@TomLlamasABC contrasts Pres. Trump's margin of victory in key swing states in 2016 with @FiveThirtyEight's current polling averages. Watch: https://t.co/qRMoWiBWGD #Debates2020 https://t.co/mEd6atS9wg

name: ABC
text:
Heading into the first presidential debate, the @FiveThirtyEight presidential election forecast has Joe Biden with a 78 in 100 chance of winning the Electoral College—but the outcome is a long way from certain.

EXPLORE: https://t.co/CGKTAk4Ty7 https://t.co/xVQx6b1y2P

name: ABC
text: Chris Wallace: "For the record, I decided the topics and the questions in each topic. I can assure you, none of the questions has been shared with the [Commission on Presidential Debates], or the two candidates." https://t.co/5Bl4Ob3O2t #Debates2020 https://t.co/5R3MixgpJs

name: ABC
text: The first question is on the Supreme Court vacancy. Americans by a nearly 20-point margin say the next Supreme Court justice should be left to the election winner and a Senate vote next year, a new @ABC News/WaPo poll found. https://t.co/CWAFxGN75M #Debates2020

name: ABC
text: Asked to respond to charges that Republicans are trying to jam through a Supreme Court appointment in the closing weeks of a presidential race, Pres. Trump says, "Very simply: We won the election. Elections have consequences." https://t.co/5Bl4Ob3O2t #Debates2020 https://t.co/lELoHHI3DZ

name: ABC
text:
The first question by debate host Chris Wallace is about the Supreme Court fight and it goes to both candidates: “Why are you right about the argument you make … and where do you think a Justice Barrett will take the court?”

 Live updates: https://t.co/5Bl4Ob3O2t #Debates2020 https://t.co/xLUJsdu674

name: ABC
text: As the candidates are pressed on health care and COVID-19, see where Joe Biden and Pres. Donald Trump stand on the issue of health. https://t.co/kUAW54cTqS #Debate2020 https://t.co/3M3gFGamAp

name: ABC
text:
President Trump defends GOP push to vote on a Supreme Court nominee ahead of the election: “We won the election and we have the right to do it.”

“The American people have a right to have a say who the Supreme Court nominee is,” Biden says. https://t.co/5Bl4Ob3O2t #Debates2020 https://t.co/afRp8ySRyD

name: ABC
text:
"My party is me," Joe Biden says to charge from Pres. Trump that his party disagrees with him on health care proposals.

"Right now, I am the Democratic Party...the platform of the Democratic Party is what I, in fact, approved of." https://t.co/5Bl4Ob3O2t #Debates2020 https://t.co/8AYkclBrAp

name: ABC
text: Pres. Trump responding to former Vice Pres. Biden's criticism on him trying to fill vacant Supreme Court seat: "I'm not elected for three years. I'm elected for four years." https://t.co/5Bl4Ob3O2t #Debates2020 https://t.co/66g8a51BJ0

name: ABC
text: Looking to catch every moment of tonight's hotly anticipated presidential debate? Stream it live on @Hulu via @ABCNewsLive. https://t.co/d9ohp2cGI2 https://t.co/c6U3oJcSnC

name: ABC
text:
Former VP Biden on Pres. Trump: "The fact is that everything he's saying so far is simply a lie. I'm not here to call out his lies. Everybody knows he's a liar."

Pres. Trump: "Joe, you're the liar. Last in your class, not first in your class" https://t.co/5Bl4Ob3O2t #Debates2020 https://t.co/gCRBTS2jjx

name: ABC
text:
As Pres. Trump repeatedly interrupts Joe Biden, Biden says, "Will you shut up, man?"

"That was really a productive segment, wasn't it?" Biden says sarcastically. "Keep yappin', man." https://t.co/5Bl4Ob3O2t #Debates2020 https://t.co/XvNahLC1Rm

name: ABC
text: Most Americans are skeptical of Pres. Trump's performance on the COVID pandemic, disbelieving of his rhetoric on the virus and critical of what they view as his lagging approach to containing it, a recent @ABC News/Ipsos poll found. https://t.co/iUhfFtaW3m

name: ABC
text: Joe Biden: "We're for a vaccine. But I don't trust [Pres. Trump] at all, and nor do you—I know you don't. What we trust is the scientists." https://t.co/5Bl4Ob3O2t #Debates2020 https://t.co/YcYS4tu0rv

name: ABC
text:
Asked why each should be trusted to handle the COVID-19 crisis, Biden criticizes Trump for downplaying the pandemic: “The president has no plan.”

Trump points to his travel restrictions, efforts on ventilators, PPE and developing a vaccine. https://t.co/5Bl4Ob3O2t #Debates2020 https://t.co/ACYpvFVzYL

name: ABC
text:
President Trump claims COVID-19 vaccine is coming "soon": "I've spoken to the scientists that are in charge. They will have the vaccine very soon."

Former VP Biden: "Do you believe for a moment what he's telling you?" https://t.co/5Bl4Ob3O2t #Debates2020 https://t.co/uPu2RlgrCo

name: ABC
text: Joe Biden responds: "His own head of the CDC said if everybody wore a mask and social distanced between now and January, we'd probably save up to 100,000 lives. It matters." https://t.co/5Bl4Ob3O2t #Debates2020 https://t.co/l4ZcyNxNVf
